refactor!: Rename estimate tmb subcommand into estimate mutational-burden
chore: add machinery for publishing and improved caching.
fix: testcase 71 sometimes fails because formula normalization via BDD is not deterministic
feat: add divindel bias for detecting artifacts caused by diverging indels associated with the alt allele
fix: Removed check for coding variants
fix: improved divindel bias estimation precision (getting rid of false negatives due to erroneous divindel bias estimates)
feat: adaptive integration (speeding up the evaluation of complex scenarios)
feat: added VAF log fold change and comparison operators to the scenario event grammar
test: add test for local fdr
fix: fixed record count in preprocess progress logging; fixed alt allele allocation error with certain longer replacements
feat: overhauled somatic prior: the effective mutation rate serves for deciding between somatic VAF 0.0 and >0.0, beyond, a flat distribution is assumed
feat: improved, more efficient, bias computation
perf: various speed improvements for scenario evaluations
perf: do not consider empty pileups for bias preprocessing
fix: fix out of bounds error when evaluating replacement records
fix: Add check for order of records in bcf (before, coordinate sorting was implicitly assumed but not checked, leading to overflow errors upon violation)
feat: Add subcommand to infer classical genotypes from Varlociraptor's AF field.

feat: eliminate false positives and false negatives: MAPQ adjustment (adjust MAPQ by mean pileup MAPQ; this gets rid of stochastically inflated MAPQs), do not estimate strand bias if all reads come from the same strand, infer wildtype forward strand rate from non-alt reads if possible
feat!: Introduce homopolymer aware pair HMM
fix: understandable error message if BCF record contains invalid position
fix: simplified but more accurate homopolymer error model
feat: do not anymore require genome size definition in scenarios
fix: fixed determination of homopolymer indels from replacements
feat: output sampled VAF densities (in the AFD format tag)
fix: use pseudo observation to adjust MAPQ for lower depths
fix: sort events by probability for more informative VCF INFO field order
feat: accurate consideration of multiallelic variants
fix: adjust mapqs by prevalence of non-unique reads at locus.
feat: optional uniform prior for non absent variants in the scenario
fix: various model improvements and corresponding test cases
feat: refinement of homopolymer error model (for increased specificity)
fix: update to latest dependency versions
refactor: cleanup and preparation for depth observations
feat: enable "false" in event expressions, in order to explicitly specify that an event is always false.
fix: Format field header for Allele Frequency Distribution should have `Number=.`, not `Number=A`
fix: remove spurious homopolymer error calls
fix: pin strum versions (same as rust-bio)
fix: check if cfg has_u128 or not
fix: only check for homopolymer errors if the indel operation is alone in the variant
fix: test case for nested references to events in scenario specification

feat: improved formula simplification for negations which can provide  major speedups and fixes a bug where part of the VAF spectrum is not missed in evalution. Further, it is now possible to define VAF sets as mysample:{0.5,1.0} in formulas and {0.0,0.5,1.0} in universe definitions.
fix: convert empty VAF spectrum to false and ensure that an empty spectrum evaluates as zero probability
fix: improved display of VAF sets in unnormalized formulas
fix: fix insufficient data leading to probabilities of 0 leading to nulls in alignment properties
feat: report read id for each observation; this information can be used by phasing algorithms to combine evidence from multiple variants covered by the same read
feat: support for haplotype blocks as candidate variants
chore: Make UnsortedVariantFile error more informative
chore: added test cases for wrongly called alt locus bias
fix: Adhere to number specifications from VCF v4.3
fix: do not skip haplotype determination if SVTYPE tag is not present in VCF
feat: allow definition of sexes other than female or male
feat: expose testcase API in library
fix: feed reported allele freq dist from all VAF estimates, not only the MAP.
fix: constrain MAP estimates of AF to the most probable event
feat: add MATEID based recognition of connected breakends
feat: support for imprecise breakend pairs
feat: add experimental support for the estimation of contaminations

fix: temporarily disable performance optimization in realignment because it can lead to underestimated likelihoods for alleles with a distance of zero to the read, thereby destroying the proper ratio between the likelihoods
feat: ability to propagate any INFO fields that are present on candidate records (--propagate-info-fields)
feat: report number of omitted observations
feat: if present, parse EF tag and consider single end reads marked to entirely cover the originating fragment for insert size statistics.
feat: added ability to omit MAPQ adjustment for known variants (varlociraptor preprocess variants --omit-mapq-adjustment)
fix: improved plotting for contamination estimation
testcase for a false negative mnv
perf: update strum to stay in sync with rust-bio
feat: by default, use prior to guard absence or presence of variant but weight all decisions about other events just by the observations
feat!: new FDR control modes. The recommended local-smart ensures more intuitive results. The fdr-control subcommand now requires --mode to be specified.

feat!: when reporting observations, provide ref and alt support as kass raftery scores (RV=very strong ref support, AV=very strong alt support, RP=positive ref support, AP=positive alt support). This is a breaking change, as any parsing of SOBS and OBS will have to be adapted to these new two letter scores.
fix: improved debug and observation output

feat!: consider edit distance to alt allele, and infer additional third allele from read if that edit distance exceeds the expectation from sequencing error rates; in addition this introduces a breaking change to the observation output (OBS, SAOBS, and SROBS, see output documentation in online docs and header information)
feat: in FDR control, skip events that do not occur in the BCF header. Error if no event matches, warn otherwise.
feat: warn on missing ANN records in mutational burden estimation
a probable indel that is falsely called an SNV due to indel realignment
fix: fixed handling of allele frequency boundaries (avoiding NaN probabilities in some rare cases); fixed handling of upper reference bound when estimating probability of third allele

fix: add flag for stating that candidate variants are atomic (in such cases, no realignment against SNVs and MNVs should happen because nearby indels can induce false positives if they are not considered in the realignment)
fix: out of bounds error in estimation of third allele probability
fix: fix invalid identification of homopolymer error
fix: fail if insert size standard deviation is zero, because that is unrealistic and causes numeric issues
chore: test case for a false negative deletion at pos MN908947.3:517
chore: test case for a false negative deletion at pos MN908947.3:517 (after resolving alignment issue)
build: Specify strum dependency to same as rust-bio
refactor: Make collect variant mod public
refactor: Make remaining parts of variant module public
fix: fix decompression of CRAM files that rely on an external reference FASTA. Varlociraptor now uses the given reference FASTA for this decompression
fix: fix bug during calculation of read position bias
fix: improved specificity of read position bias model by estimating the rate of the predominant read position from the ref supporting observations
fix: complete overhaul of homopolymer error model (to be more specific) and fix for strand bias model (to be more sensitive)
chore: test case for a variant (variant id 104 at NC_001802.1:1205) that has higher af than expected
fix: fix handling of N-bases in reads (so far, they could have yielded wrong likelihoods)
feat: support for per variant prior heterozygosity or somatic mutation rates
fix: improve code quality using cargo fix
refactor: unify evidence (between paired end and single end) and locus handling in variants
refactor: rename evidences so that they are distinguishable from other technologies
refactor: generalize evidence name into ids that can as well be u32
fix: update to rust-htslib 0.48, thereby allowing for leading deletions in CIGAR strings
fix: heuristically adjust likelihoods of singleton evidence for a variant (across all samples only one read supporting the variant) that can equally likely be some artifact like a PCR error
refactor: rename HEURISTICS field into the more generic HINTS
feat: allow multiple input bams for estimating alignment properties
chore(deps): update ring requirement from 0.16 to 0.17
chore(deps): update statrs requirement from 0.16 to 0.18
